  "description": [
    "London Firm Barred From U S Trade on Charge of Aiding Reds By th Associated Press The Commerce Department yesterday barred a London firm from getting any more goods from this country on the ground that It had illegally reshipped to Russia 50 tor of molybdenum a steelstrengthening metal A department statement said the order applies to the Industrial Specialty Co Ltd four company officers Gerald Stanley Panchaud John Braithwaite Panchaud George Jackson and G C Stone hill and any companies they control U S Exporter Cleraed The American exporter who hipped the molybdenum to the English firm was cleared as hav ing had no knowledge or reason able ground to suspect that a re shipment to Russia from England was planned His identity was withheld In conjunction with the action against the London firm it became known that the Commerce De partment maintains a watch list of firms or traders suspected of sending goods to Russia or her satellites A Commerce Department official aid the confidential list contains about 1000 foreign names mostly those of Europeans and about 500 American names Not Black List It is not a black list this Offi cial said Whenever an application for an"
